article.description: Jordan Burns scored 27 points on 10-of-17 shooting with eight assists and Colgate beat Navy 93-71 on Saturday for its six straight win.
article.headline: Burns, Rayman lead Colgate past Navy 93-71
article.linkText: Burns, Rayman lead Colgate past Navy 93-71
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- Jordan Burns scored 27 points on 10-of-17 shooting with eight assists and Colgate beat Navy 93-71 on Saturday for its six straight win. Will Rayman added 21 points and seven rebounds for the Raiders, while Rapolas Ivanauskas chipped in 20 with eight rebounds. Tucker Richardson had six assists for Colgate (19-10, 11-5 Patriot League). Colgate made a season-high 17 3-point attempts en route to a season high 93 points. Danny Ogele had 12 points for the Midshipmen (9-18, 6-10) and George Kiernan and Cam David each scored 10 The Raiders evened the season series against the Midshipmen with the win. Navy defeated Colgate 72-66 on Jan. 3. Colgate plays Holy Cross at home on Wednesday. Navy plays Bucknell at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
